wissen zu dem in der Literatur bisher stark vernachlässigten Thema Bahnhofsbuchhandel. Er zeigt Ideen und Strategien auf, wie sich die Branche auch unter schwierigen Marktbedingungen weiter entwickeln und ihre Zukunft sichern kann.  aThe station book trade in Germany must currently face new challenges: the possible abandoning of opening hours, the shift of press sales to non-press outlets and above all, the concentration of book and press sales in large media and trading companies. Against the backdrop of historical developments, Peter Brummund analyses the specialities of this section of the book and press marketing business. He is the author of a number of important studies on this topic and has worked in the press for years, in publishing houses, and lately in his own national marketing and import business. This handbook is the first unique study of the branch offering concise knowledge on the station book trade, a subject much neglected until now. It demonstrates ideas and strategies on how the branch can develop further and secure its future even under the difficult market conditions.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Nov 2021) 0aNewspaper vendorszGermany. 0aRailroad stationszGermany. 4aDortmund. 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Journalism.2bisacsh1 aSussmann, Klaus, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Library Information Science 2000 - 2014z9783110636246oZDB-23-GLI08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK GESAMTPAKET / COMPLETE PACKAGE 2005z9783110277111oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK PAKET LIBRARY AND INFORMATION SCIENCE  2005z9783110276916oZDB-23-DGB0 cprintz978359821327440uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311092921840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110929218423Coveruhtt